{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Researchers launched further clinical investigations to study this strange behavior and discovered something that changed the dominant conception on how the human brain ultimately works.",
    "It seemed that both sides of the patients' brains that were previously united were now acting independently, like separate ''entities''!",
    "Over the years some of these experiments have been recorded on tape and we can watch them online and observe these strange phenomena in videos recorded back then, in real time [20].",
    "This led to one of the strangest ideas anyone has ever encountered in neuroscience and psychology: There are two \"beings\" that live in our heads.",
    "And we are just one of them."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
